  "text": "of nanoparticles in vitro using radiation force in combination with microbubble-loaded nanoparticle constructs compared with without using radiation force [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . linking nanoparticles to microbubbles is also advantageous because it prevents dilution of the nanoparticle solution when it enters the bloodstream [CITATION_3] . Finally, microbubbles loaded with certain nanoparticles may serve as multi-modality contrast agents for platforms such as dual MrI-ultrasound and optical-ultrasound [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , although further discussion of these methods is beyond the scope of this review.",
